/**
 * AnyFunction type represents a function that accepts any number of arguments and returns any type of value. It is used for the connector methods, interceptors, overrides and extensions for which we don't know the exact types.
 *
 * @example
 *
 * const fn: AnyFunction = (a, b) => a + b;
 */
members.name: AnyFunction
Connector
EventCallback
Extension

members.docComment:
/**
 * InitFunction is a function that is called when the module is initialized. It contains the module options that is passed to the module and returns the module.
 *
 * @example
 *
 * const MyModule: InitFunction<Module> = (opts) => { // Do something with the options return { connector: { method1: () => {}, }, } }
 */
members.name: InitFunction

members.docComment:
/**
 * Initializes SDK
 *
 * @param sdkConfig - SDK configuration
 *
 * @example
 *
 * This is an example of how to initialize SDK Providing generic type is required to get proper type inference.
 * ```typescript
 * const sdkConfig = {
 *   module1: buildModule<Module1, typeof extension>(module1, {}, extension),
 *   module2: buildModule<Module2>(module2),
 * };
 *
 * const sdk = initSDK<typeof sdkConfig>(sdkConfig);
 * ```
 *
 */
members.name: initSDK

/**
 * InterceptorsConfig represents the configuration of the interceptors. It is a map of the interceptor type to the map of the method name to the interceptor.
 *
 * @example
 *
 * const interceptorsConfig: InterceptorsConfig = { before: { method1: [interceptor1, interceptor2], method2: interceptor3, }, after: { method1: [interceptor1, interceptor2], method2: interceptor3, }, around: { method1: [interceptor1, interceptor2], method2: interceptor3, }, };
 */
